---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const phone = '(352) 292-1499';
const phoneTel = '3522921499';
const city = 'Hernando Beach';
const county = 'Hernando County';
---

<Layout 
  title={`Concrete Contractors in ${city}, FL | Driveways, Patios & Seawalls`}
  description={`Coastal concrete experts serving ${city}, Florida. Specializing in salt-resistant driveways, patios, and slabs for waterfront properties. Call ${phone}!`}
  canonical="/locations/hernando-beach/"
>
  <section class="service-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Concrete Contractors in {city}, Florida</h1>
      <p>Specialized concrete solutions for coastal and waterfront properties. Built to withstand the unique challenges of {city}'s environment.</p>
      <a href={`tel:${phoneTel}`} class="btn btn-primary">Call {phone}</a>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="intro">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="intro-grid">
        <div class="intro-content">
          <h2>Coastal Concrete Specialists for {city}</h2>
          <p>{city} is one of Hernando County's most unique communities—a waterfront paradise where residents enjoy canal-front living with access to the Gulf of Mexico. This beautiful setting also presents specific challenges for concrete work that require specialized knowledge and techniques.</p>
          
          <p>At Brooksville Concrete Co., we have extensive experience working on Hernando Beach properties. From salt-resistant concrete formulations to proper drainage design for waterfront lots, we understand what it takes to create durable concrete surfaces in a coastal environment.</p>
          
          <p>Whether you need a new driveway that can handle boat trailers, a patio for enjoying waterfront sunsets, or a solid slab for your workshop, we deliver concrete work that's engineered for Hernando Beach's demanding conditions.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="intro-content">
          <h3>Coastal Concrete Services</h3>
          <ul class="why-list">
            <li>
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
              <div>
                <strong>Waterfront Driveways</strong>
                Heavy-duty driveways designed to handle boat trailers and withstand salt air exposure.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
              <div>
                <strong>Canal-Side Patios</strong>
                Create the perfect space for waterfront entertaining with slip-resistant concrete finishes.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
              <div>
                <strong>Boat Ramp Pads</strong>
                Reinforced concrete pads for boat lifts, ramps, and waterfront equipment.
              </div>
            </li>
            <li>
              <svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 16.17L4.83 12l-1.42 1.41L9 19 21 7l-1.41-1.41z"/></svg>
              <div>
                <strong>Elevated Foundations</strong>
                Slabs and foundations designed for flood zone requirements and coastal conditions.
              </div>
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="service-content">
    <h2>Specialized Concrete for {city}'s Unique Environment</h2>
    
    <p>Hernando Beach isn't like other Hernando County communities. The salt air, high water table, and flood zone considerations all require specialized concrete approaches. Our team has worked extensively in Hernando Beach, developing techniques that address these specific challenges.</p>

    <h3>Salt Air and Corrosion Resistance</h3>
    
    <p>Salt air is one of the biggest enemies of concrete in coastal areas. It can accelerate deterioration of both the concrete surface and any reinforcing steel within. For Hernando Beach projects, we use specific concrete formulations and sealers that provide enhanced protection against salt damage.</p>
    
    <p>Our approach includes using higher-strength concrete mixes, proper air entrainment for freeze-thaw resistance (yes, it occasionally gets cold in Florida!), and quality sealers that create a barrier against salt penetration. These measures significantly extend the life of your concrete investment.</p>

    <h3>Waterfront Property Challenges</h3>
    
    <p>Most Hernando Beach properties feature canal frontage, which means dealing with high water tables and potential flooding concerns. We address these challenges through:</p>
    
    <ul>
      <li>Proper site grading to direct water away from structures</li>
      <li>Adequate concrete thickness for waterfront loads (boat trailers, etc.)</li>
      <li>Strategic joint placement to accommodate soil movement</li>
      <li>Appropriate reinforcement for the specific application</li>
      <li>Coordination with flood zone requirements where applicable</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Heavy-Duty Applications for Boaters</h3>
    
    <p>Many Hernando Beach residents are boaters, which means driveways and pads need to handle significant loads. Boat trailers, especially those carrying larger vessels, put substantial stress on concrete surfaces. We engineer our Hernando Beach installations to handle these demands without cracking or settling.</p>
    
    <p>Beyond just thickness, we pay attention to surface finish. A slip-resistant texture is essential for safety when launching and retrieving boats. We can also install dedicated wash-down areas with proper drainage for cleaning your boat after trips to the Gulf.</p>

    <h3>Decorative Options for Waterfront Living</h3>
    
    <p>Just because Hernando Beach concrete needs to be durable doesn't mean it can't be beautiful. We offer a full range of decorative concrete options including stamped patterns, exposed aggregate, and colored concrete. Imagine a stamped concrete patio in a natural stone pattern, perfect for enjoying sunsets over the canal.</p>
    
    <p>Our decorative concrete options include slip-resistant finishes ideal for pool decks and waterfront areas. You can have both beauty and safety in your Hernando Beach outdoor spaces.</p>

    <h3>Serving All of {city}</h3>
    
    <p>From the homes along Hernando Beach Boulevard to the canal-side properties throughout the community, we provide consistent, quality concrete services. We understand the unique character of Hernando Beach and work with homeowners to create concrete surfaces that enhance both function and property value.</p>
    
    <p>If your Hernando Beach property needs concrete work—whether it's replacing an existing surface or new construction—contact Brooksville Concrete Co. for a free consultation. Call <a href={`tel:${phoneTel}`}>{phone}</a> to get started.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="cta">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Coastal Concrete Experts for {city}</h2>
      <p>Concrete solutions designed for waterfront living</p>
      <a href={`tel:${phoneTel}`} class="btn">Call {phone} Now</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
